2) Evaluation of the two candidates against those criteria:
- Kind of Blue (Jazz; Bebop) — A 1959 Miles Davis album widely regarded as a landmark in jazz and one of the most influential albums in 20th-century music. It is a cohesive, mood-driven set of modal jazz pieces (e.g., "So What", "Freddie Freeloader", "All Blues", "Blue in Green", "Flamenco Sketches") featuring major players (Miles Davis, John Coltrane, Cannonball Adderley, Bill Evans). Its improvisational depth, subtle interplay, and consistent atmosphere make it an album that rewards focused, repeated listening and benefits from the clarity and continuity that the CD format provides.
