3) Why I chose Kind of Blue and rejected HIStory:
- Choice rationale: Since my stated interest is simply that I "enjoy listening to CDs very much," I prioritize albums that make the most of the CD listening experience: coherent sequencing, musical depth, and replay value. Kind of Blue is historically and musically notable for its consistent mood, interplay among legendary musicians, and compositions that reveal more on repeated listens. These qualities align well with an enthusiastic CD listener seeking an immersive album experience rather than a collection of singles.
- Reasons for rejecting HIStory: HIStory is an important and commercially successful pop release with many strong singles, but its double-disc structure (greatest-hits plus newer pop/dance tracks and remixes) makes it feel more like a compilation geared to individual songs and chart performance. That format is less aligned with the criterion of a unified, depth-filled album experience that tends to be most rewarding for dedicated CD listening sessions. For those reasons—favoring album cohesion, sustained musical nuance, and replay depth—I select Kind of Blue.

