- Advantage balance: Peachtree Road does have many redeeming qualities (transient preservation, restrained compression, punchy supportive low end), but on balance those plus the lush, album‑oriented presentation leave it less aligned to my core priorities than the singles package.
In sum, the Concise 2–3‑minute singles better fulfill the majority of my stated, specific preferences: centered, immediate vocals; controlled compression and preserved micro‑dynamics; tight three‑part harmonies; concise, phrase‑driven song structure; minimal smear and uncluttered instrumentation. Peachtree Road has appealing analogue and transient qualities, but its album‑centric, lush/live presentation risks the exact issues I listed as dislikes (less concise editing, potential for orchestration or roominess that softens vocal immediacy), so I reject it in favor of the singles.

